<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1096">
Your task is to calculate the number of ways to get a sum $n$ by throwing dice. Each throw yields an integer between $1 \ldots 6$.<br />
<br />
For example, if $n=10$, some possible ways are $3+3+4$, $1+4+1+4$ and $1+1+6+1+1$.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line contains an integer $n$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print the number of ways modulo $10^9+7$.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 10^{18}$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>8</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>125</code>    </div>
